Evaluation¶

1. Evaluate goodput and queuing delay for multiple settings in one using static flows.¶

One variant for reference delay 2ms and one for 200s. For each variant

  • Gold and Silver static connections, 1 each, 5 each, 10 each and 50 each.
    • For each connection variant do 1 "pillar" for
      • m=8 and c=2^10, CTV update interval 1 s
      • m=8 and c=2^10, CTV update interval 5ms
      • m=13 and c=2^14, CTV update interval 1 s
      • m=13 and c=2^14, CTV update interval 5ms
    • Each pillar should show difference between gold and silver. Done by stacking on top of eachother.
  • Queuing delay CDF for each variant in previous variant.
    • Plot the probability that the queuing delay is at value X or lower. Chose an interval depending on reference delay perhaps.

Evaluation¶

All tests can be found in Test_PacketInfo.txt

3. The following tests will evaluate queuing delay and flow fairness.¶

  • The following assumptions are made:
    • m represents table size.
    • c represents counter size.
    • The ECDF update timer in the Control Plane is set to 0.
    • is set to 0.3125 and is set to 3.125, unless otherwise specified.

First a baseline test is introduced as test 1.

The settings for the baseline test is then slightly modified in test 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6.

Test 7 uses the setting used in the original PIE implementation.

Test 8 and 9 takes two settings from previous tests and adds 5 flows of each type each 10 seconds.

Test 10 and 11 uses the same settings as 8 and 9 but with c = 2^14 and to add 5 flows of each type each 1 second. The goal of test 10 and 11 is to add new flows faster than how often the ECDF is updated in the control plane, which for c = 2^14, is larger than 1s (as seen in "Read_recorded_registerValues"). Additionally, test 10 and 11 stops adding new flows after 30s.

Test 12 attempts to do the same as 10 and 11, but with c = 2^10, with 1 new flow added each 50ms for 10 seconds. Test 13 is run with an deactivates the AQM, as a point of reference.

1. Baseline test.¶

  • Name: "TEST_EvX_MC1_C1D1_P1_I1_T1_1"
  • Starts with 10 flows of gold and 10 flows silver.
    • MC1: m = 8, c = 2^10.
    • C1D1: CTV update interval = 10s, reference delay = 2ms.
    • P1: Port shaping 1gig.
    • I1: No added flows.
    • T1: Test time = 30s
